        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Actually a user can provide any path, containing any class to setBootStrap() , it will just blindly try to make an instance of it.\n\nWhen loading the path, It doesn't check that the file contains the right class.\nWhen instantiating the class, it doesn't check before that it's a Zend_Application_Bootstrap_Bootstrapper class, which introduces a bug.\n\nThe patch is attached, can matthew or Zend person review it that way I can commit it with the appropriates tests ?"
        },
